headline: How The Palo Alto Networks (PANW) Story Is Shifting As Valuation Cools And AI Deals Grow
summary: Palo Alto Networks just saw its modeled fair value trimmed from US$226.65 to US$209.61, a change that reflects a more cautious stance on the stock’s potential upside. Analysts are still pointing to resilient cybersecurity demand and steady execution, but are pairing that with more restrained targets as sector sentiment cools and valuation multiples reset. As you read on, you will see how these shifting views could shape the story for Palo Alto Networks and what to watch as the narrative...
